[section className:"article-body"]
On the other hand, would Minerva's financial aid system remain solvent if it did try to protect students from such risk? Would Minerva still be able to admit so many international students in need of financial aid if Minerva did consider forex risks posed to non-American students? 

These are some of the challenging questions that Minerva's community wrestles with as students continue to lobby for reforms to the financial aid system.


